abstract: Insults and indignation were served up Thursday in the House Judiciary Committee. Republicans worried they would not get to the White House ball in time.
snippet: Insults and indignation were served up Thursday in the House Judiciary Committee. Republicans worried they would not get to the White House ball in time.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — “Wait, is it going to be like this all day?”

headline_main: Highlights From House Committee Debate on Articles of Impeachment

abstract: Jared Kushner, who is overseeing his father-in-law’s re-election campaign, said the Republican Party was being redefined with the “old guard cycling out” and the people coming in “inspired by the Trump revolution.”
snippet: Jared Kushner, who is overseeing his father-in-law’s re-election campaign, said the Republican Party was being redefined with the “old guard cycling out” and the people coming in “inspired by the Trump revolution.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hours before the House Judiciary Committee was set to take a historic vote to push President Trump to the brink of impeachment, campaign officials gathered across the Potomac River for a state-of-the-race briefing in which they described how the Republican Party had been transformed into the “beer and bluejeans party” crafted in Mr. Trump’s image.

abstract: A hearing in Virginia was the first time a full appeals panel has considered the anticorruption clauses of the Constitution.
snippet: A hearing in Virginia was the first time a full appeals panel has considered the anticorruption clauses of the Constitution.
lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — A federal appeals court in Virginia heard arguments Thursday about whether to revive a lawsuit accusing President Trump of violating the Constitution by profiting from his hotel near the White House, in a spirited session that indicated sharp divisions among the judges over the legal consequences of the president’s conduct.

abstract: President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field can compete with the incumbent.
snippet: President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field ca...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump’s reelection campaign on Thursday shrugged off the president's expected impeachment less than a year before Election Day, talking up the campaign's data collection efforts and declaring that no one in the Democratic field can compete with the incumbent.
headline_main: Playing Down Impeachment, Trump Campaign Voices Confidence
headline_print_headline: Playing Down Impeachment, Trump Campaign Voices Confidence

abstract: He won’t be on the debate stage next week. But he says his campaign continues, “debate or not.”
snippet: He won’t be on the debate stage next week. But he says his campaign continues, “debate or not.”
lead_paragraph: In less than six hours, we will know who’s officially made the cut for next week’s Democratic primary debate.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
headline_main: Biden Lands Early Slate of Former Backers of Harris' Presidential Bid
headline_print_headline: Biden Lands Early Slate of Former Backers of Harris' Presidential Bid

abstract: Senior negotiators in the U.S. Congress on Thursday reached a tentative deal with the White House on a series of bills to fund federal agencies through Sept. 30, 2020, which would avert partial government shutdowns next week.
snippet: Senior negotiators in the U.S. Congress on Thursday reached a tentative deal with the White House on a series of bills to fund federal agencies through Sept. 30, 2020, which would avert partial government shutdowns next week.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior negotiators in the U.S. Congress on Thursday reached a tentative deal with the White House on a series of bills to fund federal agencies through Sept. 30, 2020, which would avert partial government shutdowns next week.
headline_main: U.S. Congress Negotiators, White House Set Tentative Deal on Fiscal 2020 Funding
